<p>Well, for the love of Shatner what is the best strategy (besides throwing millions of dollars at a professional PR firm to astroturf the opposition)? I know I can present evidence and studies and reasoned debate till I'm blue in the face, but that's pretty boring stuff. I've learned by experience that there's no way to drill through the truthiness of pop culture conspiracy theories because they're romantic and exciting. Lots of people think science is boring stuff for eggheads and pocket protectors and playing D&D (of course, I live in Virginia so this is to be expected). Like Nero Wolfe, I cannot open their skulls to remove the offending brain cells. </p>
