<p>Any discussion of meta-effects, such as an individual's ability to judge expertise in multiple domains? For example, someone who knows a great deal about physics, very competent in that domain: how does such a person judge their own competence in an orthogonal domain such as (to pick at random) Christian exegesis? (see, I can't even spell it correctly)</p>

<p>I suspect that we *all* fall prey to this effect... but I could be wrong. I'm often wrong. </p>
