	<div class="commentcontent">
		<p>The next time someone tries to offer you a solution to a hard problem, listen for his/her use of the word "just".  As in "Just do X" or "First do Y and then it's just a matter of Z".  90% of the time, use of "just" is a clear indication of speaker ignorance.  The other 10%, the person actually has the necessary experience to recognize the solution.  There doesn't seem to be any middle ground.</p>
	</div>
</div>


        
    
        
